<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND SLEEVES - PISTON AND ROD
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PISTON AND ROD ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
            <title>INSTALLATION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the piston rings with clean engine oil and stagger the ring gaps 120&#176;
                    apart.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the piston ring compressor over the piston rings.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the cylinder sleeve with clean engine oil.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The piston and rod assemblies can be installed by turning the crankshaft three times.
                            Position the No. 1 and 6 crankpins at BDC. Install the No. 1 and 6 piston assemblies. Repeat
                            this procedure for the Nos. 2 and 5 and Nos. 3 and 4 piston and rod assemblies.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the piston and rod assembly into the sleeve. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150658">6.58</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . The numbers on the rod must face away from the camshaft while the markings on top of the piston
                    faces toward the camshaft side of the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the piston into the sleeve with a wooden handle. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150659">6.59</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Guide the connecting rod into place on the crankpin. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150660">6.60</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150658" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11663" filename="../figcg1/CG11663.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.58. Place Piston and Rod into Cylinder Sleeve.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150659" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12134" filename="../figcg1/CG12134.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.59. Insert Piston into Sleeve.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150660" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11572" filename="../figcg1/CG11572.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.60. Guide Rods onto Crankpin.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
